<TITLE> Govt appoints new press minister in DC </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 31 (bdnews24.com)  The establishment ministry on Sunday appointed Swapan Saha, chief news editor of Bangladesh Shongbad Shongstha (BSS), as the new press minister of Bangladesh's embassy at Washington DC. The former press minister Akhter Ahmed Khan died in December from heart attack and the position had remained vacant since then. The appointment order said that Swapan Saha would serve on contractual basis for two years from the date he joins this new job. 
